{
  "text": "The net heat flux over our study period is 32 6 4 W m 22 (Table 1 and Figure 3 ). This flux is considerably smaller than the net heat flux of 44 6 5 W m 22 observed by [CITATION_1] . The decreased net heat flux is mostly due to an increase in ocean latent heat loss, although a reduction in incoming shortwave radiation and an increase in ocean long wave cooling also contributes (Table 1) ",
